<%= render :partial => 'shared/appear' -%>

<div id="appear">
  <div id='header'>
    You're the Spotlight
  </div>

  <div id='stage'>
    <a href='#player1text' rel='facebox'><img src='/images/spotlight/Character-Boy.png' id='player1' /></a>
    <a href='#player2text' rel='facebox'><img src='/images/spotlight/Character-Cat-Girl.png' id='player2' /></a>
    <a href='#'><img src='/images/spotlight/Character-Pink-Girl.png' id='player3' /></a>
  </div>

  <div id="player1text" style="display:none;"> 
    That's it then, is it? We've done nothing wrong. We didn't harm anybody, did we?
  </div>

  <div id='player2text' style='display:none;'>
    There must have been a moment at the beginning, where we could have said no. Somehow we missed it. Well, we'll know better next time. 
  </div>

  <div id='director'>
    <a href='#'>Action #1</a>
    <a href='#'>Action #2</a>
    <a href='#'>Action #3</a>
    <a href='#'>Action #4</a>
    <a href='#'>Action #5</a>
  </div>

  <div id='footer'>
    All the world's a stage and all the men & women merely spotlights.
  </div>
</div>

<script type='text/javascript'>
  $(document).ready(function(){
    $('#player3').click(function(){
      $(this).spotlight();
    });
  });
</script>
